KEYWORDS Malaria Travel medicine Fever Diagnostics Antiparasitic therapy Chemoprophylaxis Malaria is common worldwide and travel to malaria-endemic destinations is increasing. Travel history should be obtained for all children presenting with fever. Antigen-based malaria tests can provide rapid malaria diagnosis, although blood smears are still necessary. Treatment of malaria depends on severity of illness, species of malaria parasite, and epidemiologic likelihood of drug resistance. 